4 All administrative regulations shall comply with the provisions of KRS 13A.222 and
5 13A.224.
6 (1) (a) An administrative body shall file with the regulations compiler:
7 1. The original and five (5) copies of an administrative regulation; and
8 2. At the same time as, or prior to, filing the paper version, an electronic
9 version of the administrative regulation and required attachments saved
10 as a single document for each administrative regulation in an electronic
11 format approved by the regulations compiler.
12 (b) If there are differences between the paper copy and the electronic version of
13 an administrative regulation filed with the regulations compiler, the electronic
14 version shall be the controlling version.
15 (2) The original and four (4) copies of each administrative regulation shall be stapled in
16 the top left corner. The fifth copy of each administrative regulation shall not be
17 stapled. The original and the five (5) copies of each administrative regulation shall
18 be grouped together.
19 (3) An amendment to an administrative regulation shall not be made on a copy of the
20 administrative regulation reproduced from the Kentucky Administrative
21 Regulations Service or the Administrative Register. It shall be a typed original in
22 the format specified in subsection (4) of this section.
23 (4) The format of an administrative regulation shall be as follows:
24 (a) An administrative regulation shall be typewritten on white paper, size eight
25 and one-half (8-1/2) by eleven (11) inches and shall be double-spaced through
26 the last line of the body of the administrative regulation. The first page shall
27 have a two (2) inch top margin. The administrative regulation shall be typed
