11 (5) The numbering within the body of an administrative regulation shall be the
12 responsibility of the promulgating body, subject to the authority of the regulations
13 compiler to divide or renumber an administrative regulation. The following format
14 shall be used by the administrative body in the numbering of each administrative
15 regulation. Each section shall begin with the word "Section" followed by an Arabic
16 number, and titles of sections shall be initially capitalized. Subsections shall be
17 designated by an Arabic number in parentheses. Paragraphs shall be designated by
18 lower case letters of the alphabet in parentheses (e.g., (a), (b), (c), etc.).
19 Subparagraphs shall be designated by an Arabic number followed by a period (e.g.,
20 1., 2., etc.). Clauses shall be designated by lower case letters of the alphabet
21 followed by a period (e.g., a., b., c., etc.). Subclauses shall be designated by lower
22 case Roman numerals in parentheses (e.g., (i), (ii), (iii), etc.). A section shall not be
23 divided into subsections, paragraphs, subparagraphs, clauses, or subclauses if there
24 is only one (1) item in that level of division.
